    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>EXTENDED INSPECTION DEADLINE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By KAREN DeMASTERS</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Demasters, Karen</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Environmental Protection Agency grants New Jersey Division of Motor Vehicles another extension, until August 1, for putting in place enhanced emissions tests at all motor vehicle inspection stations (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The federal Environmental Protection Agency last week granted the Division of Motor Vehicles another extension of the deadline -- to Aug. 1 -- for getting the enhanced emissions tests in place at all motor vehicle inspection stations, said Mary Mears, an E.P.A. spokeswoman. A few of the stations that have only one or two lanes still cannot perform the enhanced emissions tests. The state said it needed the delay beyond the original June 30 deadline to set up an appointment system at those stations to avoid long lines for the enhanced tests.</p>
        <p>KAREN DeMASTERS</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
